"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1059964","Cabinet Office","false","2019-02-18","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith",,"2019-02-18T14:17:56.587Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1059964/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1059964/answer","PQ 220061 & 220062 - Uploaded (1).pdf","UKSA Response","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1059964/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2019-02-12","Crime: West Midlands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many reported (a) homicides, (b) instances of fraud and forgery and (c) sexual offences there have been in the West Midlands police force area in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","220062"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1059966","Department for Transport","false","2019-02-18","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the Answer I gave to PQ UIN 219568.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2019-02-18T15:29:08.153Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1059966/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1059966/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1059966/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-02-12","Channel Ferries: Freight","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, with reference to the Written Statement of 7 January 2019, Haulage Update, HCWS 1233, what costs have been incurred by his Department as a result of (a) due diligence and external cost consultants and (b) legal advice and services.","false","Biography information for Alan Brown","Kilmarnock and Loudoun","Alan Brown","220290"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1059967","Home Office","false","2019-02-18","<p>It is not possible to make direct comparisons between these years due to changes in police funding arrangements over the period. Information on historic police funding can be found in our statistical bulletin published at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/police-funding-for-england-and-wales-2015-to-2019%20" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/police-funding-for-england-and-wales-2015-to-2019 </a>which explains the changes in the structure of police funding.</p><p>Details of the police funding settlement for forces in England and Wales, is published annually at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/police-finance" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/police-finance</a>. The funding settlement for 2019/20, agreed by Parliament on 5 February, provides up to £970 million of additional funding for the police, including the pensions grant and income from council tax precept. In the West Midlands, this means funding of up to £568.6 million, an increase of up to £34.3 million from 2018/19.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2019-02-18T15:43:29.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1059967/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1059967/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1059967/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-02-12","Police: Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the change in level of funding for the police force in (a) England and (b) the West Midlands has been in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","220063"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1059968","Home Office","false","2019-02-22","<p>My Department is in regular contact with the Welsh Government on a range of policies, including those relating to drugs and the recent drugs review. The correspondence and calls are undertaken on a confidential basis and it would not be appropriate to publish details.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2019-02-22T13:21:09.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1059968/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1059968/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1059968/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-02-12","Drugs: Reviews","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if he will publish all correspondence and telephone transcripts between the UK Government and the Welsh Government on the terms of reference of the Independent review of drugs.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Edwards","Carmarthen East and Dinefwr","Jonathan Edwards","220182"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1059970","Department for Transport","false","2019-02-18","<p>On 25 January 2019 the Channel Tunnel Group Ltd and France-Manche SA (“Eurotunnel”) brought two claims against the Secretary of State for Transport by way of judicial review and under the Public Contracts Regulations 2015. We are not aware of any other claims against the Department.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2019-02-18T15:55:23.093Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1059970/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1059970/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1059970/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-02-12","Channel Ferries: Freight","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 24 January 2019 to Question 210667 on Channel Ferries: Freight, how many companies that made representations (a) formally lodged, (b) indicated an intention to lodge and (c) decided not to lodge court procedings; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Alan Brown","Kilmarnock and Loudoun","Alan Brown","220291"
